        "title": "fix(openrouter): guard music generation SSE JSON.parse against malformed frames",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`extensions/openrouter/music-generation-provider.ts:128` calls `JSON.parse(data)` on SSE data frames without try/catch. A malformed SSE data frame → unhandled `SyntaxError` → music generation crashes instead of skipping the bad frame.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/openrouter/music-generation-provider.ts`: wrap `JSON.parse(data)` in try/catch → `return false` (skip frame) on malformed SSE data\n- `extensions/openrouter/music-generation-provider.test.ts`: test verifying malformed SSE frames are skipped and valid audio frames still processed\n\nLabel: bugfix | merge-risk: 🟢 minimal | AI-assisted\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Unit test — exercises actual SSE processing code path\n\nThe test `skips malformed SSE data frames and processes valid audio frames` sends mixed malformed + valid SSE frames through `generateMusic()` → `processOpenRouterSseLine`. The mocked SSE stream contains `data: NOT JSON {{{` followed by a valid audio frame. This exercises the exact changed try/catch path.\n\n```\n$ pnpm exec vitest run extensions/openrouter/music-generation-provider.test.ts\n\n ✓ skips malformed SSE data frames and processes valid audio frames\n ... (all existing tests pass)\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  9 passed (9)\n   Duration  49.19s\n```\n\n### Patch logic\n\n`processOpenRouterSseLine` receives `data:` lines. Before: `JSON.parse(data)` on malformed frame → SyntaxError → crash. After: malformed frames return `false` (skip), same as empty data — valid audio frames in the same stream are still decoded.",
